). In a recent study, serveral prenylated flavonoids ( 500–506 ) ( Fig. 20 ) ( Table 12 ) were isolated from the leaves of
Morus yunnanensis (Moraceae)
and their tyrosinase inhibitory activity was evaluated by using the spectrophotometric method (
). Among these compounds, compounds 502 , 503 and 504 showed potent inhibitory activity with IC 50 values ranging from 0.12 ± 0.02 to 1.43 ± 0.43 μM. Particularly, it was worth noting that the IC 50 value of compound 503 (0.15 μM) was 217-fold lower than the kojic acid (32.62 μM). Based on these data, prenylated flavonoids bearing the 2 ′ ,4’-(OH) 2 on the B ring seems crucial to the tyrosinase inhibitory activity.

