3 ′ ,5 ′ -cyclic monophosphate (cGMP) and phosphodiesterase 5 (PDE5) play a significant role in modulating smooth muscle tone in general, and the inhibitors of cGMP PDE5 have greater efficacy for the treatment of erectile dysfunction (
). During the search for cGMP-PDE5 inhibitors, Tabopda et al. found that the extracts from
Sophora flavescens (Leguminosae)
exhibited potent inhibitory activity, and they obtained five prenylated flavonoids ( 516–520 ) ( Fig. 20 ) from the plants, subsequently their inhibitory activity against cGMP-PDE5 was evaluated ( Table 12 ) (
). The result indicated that these compounds exhibited potent cGMP-PDE5 inhibitory activity with IC 50 values ranging from 0.03 to 10.6 μM. It was worth noting that sophoflavescenol ( 519 ), a C-8 prenylated flavonol, showed the most potent inhibitory activity (IC 50 = 0.013 μM) against cGMP-PDE5, which suggested that the prenylated flavonoids can be considered as a lead structure for the future synthesis of potent cGMP-PDE5 inhibitors with probably more desirable pharmacological profiles.

Neuraminidase mainly promote mucosal infection via biofilm formation which is closely related to bacterial infection, and it also appears to be a proven target in anti-viral drug development (
;
